Professional Summary: 
 As a Senior SAP EWM Consultant, leads the design and implementation of SAP EWM solutions for large-scale warehousing operations. Collaborates with stakeholders to gather requirements, configure EWM modules, and provide strategic guidance to optimize warehouse processes.
Skills : SAP EWM Configuration, Warehouse Management, Inventory Management, Supply Chain Management
Key Responsibilities:
Þ Engage proactively with clients and participate in daily status meetings with business teams to identify, escalate, track, and resolve the issues within timelines.
Þ Analyzed warehouse processes to optimize efficiency and reduce costs, and configured EWM modules to meet specific business requirements and needs.
Þ Developed and implemented strategies to improve warehouse operational workflows.
Þ Integrated SAP EWM with other systems to streamline operations seamlessly.
Þ Conducted user training sessions on SAP EWM functionalities and features, and managed system upgrades and patches to maintain optimal performance levels.
Þ Created detailed documentation for EWM configuration and implementation processes.
Þ Implemented SAP Extended Warehouse Management (EWM) solutions for various clients, significantly enhancing their inventory management and warehouse operations.
Þ Conducted thorough analysis of existing warehouse processes to identify areas for improvement and to design tailored EWM solutions that meet specific business needs.
Þ Experience in advanced functionalities of EWM like slotting, rearrangement, cross docking, yard management, material flow control, value added service(vas) and transport management(tm).
Þ EWM- TM Integration knowledge and Kitting, cartonization  planning.
Þ Good Exposure in HU, TU,Batch management processes.
Þ Good Knowledge in end-to-end EWM functional processes.
Þ Ensured compliance with industry standards and regulations in EWM processes.
Þ Experience in all functionalities including logistics execution of inbound, outbound, and internal movements. MFS, Automated Guided vehicle(AGV)
Þ Knowledge in interfaces, web services connectivity (ALE, EDI, IDoc) to SAP and non-SAP system.
Þ Integration with other modules like MM, PP, SD, and QM with EWM is necessary.
Þ  Facilitated change management activities related to EWM system updates.
Þ Led the migration of legacy warehouse management systems to SAP EWM, ensuring data integrity and minimal downtime during the transition.
Þ Integrated SAP EWM with other SAP modules such as SAP S/4HANA and SAP TM to create a cohesive supply chain management environment.
